 for architectural thinking vs. execution. They=E2=80=99ve recognized that =
memory needs differ by task type, not just by volume.
The pattern: Every major player is racing to solve memory, but they=E2=80=
=99re solving different slices of it. ChatGPT Memory won=E2=80=99t talk to =
Claude. Cursor=E2=80=99s memory bank is great=E2=80=94until you need to swi=
tch editors. No single vendor has the full solution yet.
And critically, you can=E2=80=99t outsource memory to a vendor, because ven=
dors don=E2=80=99t understand your context well enough to truly solve it (a=
nd why should you turn memory over to one vendor?)
